height here.

00:07:17.210 --> 00:07:18.550
Integrating with
respect to dx.

00:07:18.550 --> 00:07:21.770
So sort of continuously
with respect to dx.

00:07:21.770 --> 00:07:25.030
Well, what is that?

00:07:25.030 --> 00:07:29.380
Well, according to the rule,
it's 1 / b - a times - sorry,

00:07:29.380 --> 00:07:30.470
it's up here in the box.

00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:34.080
1 / b - a, the interval from
a to b, f ( x) dx.

00:07:34.080 --> 00:07:39.460
That's 1 / + 1 - (- 1).

00:07:39.460 --> 00:07:45.240
The integral from - 1 to 1,
square root of 1 - x ^2 dx.

00:07:45.240 --> 00:07:52.727
Right, because the height is y
= , this is y = the square

00:07:52.727 --> 00:07:57.260
root of 1 - x^2.

00:07:57.260 --> 00:08:02.990
And to evaluate this is not as
difficult as it seems. This is

00:08:02.990 --> 00:08:06.950
1/2 times this quantity
here, which we can

00:08:06.950 --> 00:08:08.940
interpret as an area.

00:08:08.940 --> 00:08:12.520
It's the area of
the semicircle.

00:08:12.520 --> 00:08:20.310
So this is the area of the
semicircle, which we know to

00:08:20.310 --> 00:08:22.730
be half the area
of the circle.

00:08:22.730 --> 00:08:26.700
So it's pi / 2.

00:08:26.700 --> 00:08:35.500
And so the answer, here the
average height, is pi/ 4.

00:08:35.500 --> 00:08:38.670
Now, later in the class and
actually not in this unit,

00:08:38.670 --> 00:08:40.660
we'll actually be able
to calculate the

00:08:40.660 --> 00:08:42.910
antiderivative of this.

00:08:42.910 --> 00:08:44.440
So in other words, we'll be
able to calculate this

00:08:44.440 --> 00:08:45.090
analytically.

00:08:45.090 --> 00:08:48.980
For right now we just have the
geometric reason why the value

00:08:48.980 --> 00:08:51.190
of this is pi / 2.

00:08:51.190 --> 00:08:53.620
And we'll do that in the fourth
unit when we do a lot

00:08:53.620 --> 00:08:57.140
of techniques of integration.

00:08:57.140 --> 00:08:58.290
So here's an example.

00:08:58.290 --> 00:09:03.770
Turns out, the average height
of this is pi / 4.

00:09:03.770 --> 00:09:07.660
Now, the next example that I
want to give introduces a

00:09:07.660 --> 00:09:09.440
