00:09:15.870 --> 00:09:22.770
I'm going to take the average
height again.

00:09:22.770 --> 00:09:33.690
But now, with respect
to arc length.

00:09:33.690 --> 00:09:37.250
Which is usually
denoted theta.

00:09:37.250 --> 00:09:39.590
Now, this brings
up an extremely

00:09:39.590 --> 00:09:43.080
important feature of averages.

00:09:43.080 --> 00:09:47.120
Which is that you have to
specify the variable with

00:09:47.120 --> 00:09:51.290
respect to which the average
is taking place.

00:09:51.290 --> 00:09:52.870
And the answer will
be different

00:09:52.870 --> 00:09:54.620
depending on the variable.

00:09:54.620 --> 00:09:56.060
So it's not going
to be the same.

00:09:56.060 --> 00:09:58.130
Wow, can't spell the
