have much longer

00:10:44.920 --> 00:10:47.770
portions of theta length.

00:10:47.770 --> 00:10:51.760
So that the average that we're
taking when we do it with

00:10:51.760 --> 00:10:56.060
respect to theta, is going to
emphasize the low values more.

00:10:56.060 --> 00:10:58.090
They're going to be
more exaggerated.

00:10:58.090 --> 00:11:02.080
And the average should
be lower than the

00:11:02.080 --> 00:11:03.030
average that we got here.

00:11:03.030 --> 00:11:04.880
So we should expect a
different number.

00:11:04.880 --> 00:11:06.950
And it's not going to be
pi / 4, it's going to

00:11:06.950 --> 00:11:07.850
be something else.

00:11:07.850 --> 00:11:12.170
Whatever it is, it should
be smaller than pi / 4.

00:11:12.170 --> 00:11:14.200
Now, let's set up
the integral.

00:11:14.200 --> 00:11:17.100
The integral follows
the same rule.

00:11:17.100 --> 00:11:19.870
It's just 1 over the length
of the interval times the

00:11:19.870 --> 00:11:24.390
